      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "title: \"Recurrent Neural Networks\"\n",
        "subtitle: \"Modeling Sequential Data with Memory\"\n",
        "author: \"Miguel Fonseca\"\n",
        "format:\n",
        "  revealjs:\n",
        "    toc: true\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Feedforward Networks vs. Recurrent Networks\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why Do We Need RNNs?\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.columns}\n",
        "::::{.column width=\"50%\"}\n",
        "### Feedforward Networks Assume Independence\n",
        "\n",
        "For MLPs:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf x_i \\perp \\mathbf x_j\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "But many datasets are sequential!\n",
        "\n",
        "::::\n",
        "\n",
        "::::{.column width=\"50%\"}\n",
        "### Recurrent Networks Capture Dependencies\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "P(\\mathbf x_t | \\mathbf x_{t-1}, \\mathbf x_{t-2}, ..., \\mathbf x_1)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Cases where RNNs are useful:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Text\n",
        "- Speech\n",
        "- Financial time-series\n",
        "- Biological sequences\n",
        "- Sensor signals\n",
        "::::\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Applications\n",
        "\n",
        "- Language modeling\n",
        "- Machine translation\n",
        "- Speech recognition\n",
        "- Time-series forecasting\n",
        "- Genomics\n",
        "- Video processing\n",
        "\n",
        "# The Recurrent Neural Network (RNN)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Core Recurrence\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf z_t =\\mathbf W_h \\mathbf h_{t-1} + \\mathbf W_x \\mathbf x_t + \\mathbf b\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf h_t = \\sigma(\\mathbf z_t)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf y_t = \\mathbf W_y \\mathbf h_t\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Same weights reused across time.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Unrolled Through Time\n",
        "\n",
        "![Unrolled RNN](/images/rnn_unrolled.svg)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## TensorFlow: Simple RNN"
      ],
      "id": "f0aa0f8a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow import keras\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras import layers\n",
        "\n",
        "model = keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.SimpleRNN(64, return_sequences=True),\n",
        "    layers.SimpleRNN(32),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1)\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer=\"adam\", loss=\"mse\")\n",
        "model.summary()"
      ],
      "id": "1e8813e8",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Backpropagation Through Time (BPTT)\n",
        "\n",
        "Training objective:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial \\mathscr L}{\\partial \\mathbf W_h} =\\sum_{t=1}^{T}\\frac{\\partial \\mathscr L}{\\partial \\mathbf h_t}\\frac{\\partial \\mathbf h_t}{\\partial \\mathbf W_h}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "But:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial \\mathbf h_t}{\\partial \\mathbf h_{t-k}}=\\prod_{i=t-k+1}^{t}\\frac{\\partial \\mathbf h_i}{\\partial \\mathbf h_{i-1}}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "with:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial \\mathbf h_i}{\\partial \\mathbf h_{i-1}}\n",
        "=\\mathbf W_h \\cdot \\text{diag}(\\sigma'(\\mathbf z_t))\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Repeated matrix multiplication → instability.\n",
        "\n",
        "## The Vanishing Gradient Problem\n",
        "\n",
        "Simplified Recurrence\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf h_t = \\sigma(\\mathbf W_h \\mathbf h_{t-1})\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Derivative:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial \\mathbf h_t}{\\partial \\mathbf h_{t-1}}\n",
        "=\n",
        "\\mathbf W_h \\cdot \\text{diag}(\\sigma'(\\mathbf z))\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Repeated products:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\prod_{i=1}^{k} \\mathbf W_h \\boldsymbol{\\lambda}_i\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.columns}\n",
        "\n",
        "::::{.column width=\"50%\"}\n",
        "If:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\rho(\\mathbf W_h) < 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        ">Gradient vanishes.\n",
        "\n",
        "::::\n",
        "\n",
        "::::{.column width=\"50%\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "If:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\rho(\\mathbf W_h) > 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        ">Exploding gradient.\n",
        "\n",
        "::::\n",
        "\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "# Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM)\n",
        "\n",
        "## LSTM Gate Equations\n",
        "\n",
        ":::{.callout-note}\n",
        "Allow constant error flow through a memory cell.\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "**Forget gate:**\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf f_t = \\sigma\\left(\\mathbf W_f [\\mathbf h_{t-1} \\, \\mathbf x_t] + \\mathbf b_f\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Input gate:**\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf i_t = \\sigma\\left(\\mathbf W_i [\\mathbf h_{t-1} \\, \\mathbf x_t] + \\mathbf b_i\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "**Output:**\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf o_t = \\sigma\\left(\\mathbf W_o [\\mathbf h_{t-1} \\, \\mathbf x_t] + \\mathbf b_o\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Input Node**\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\widetilde{\\mathbf c} = \\tanh\\left(\\mathbf W_c [\\mathbf h_{t-1} \\, \\mathbf x_t] + \\mathbf b_c\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "![LSTM Cell Update with Input](/images/lstm-1.svg){width=70%}\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Cell update\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf c_t = \\mathbf f_t \\odot \\mathbf c_{t-1} + \\mathbf i_t \\odot \\widetilde{\\mathbf c}_t\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf h_t = \\mathbf o_t \\odot \\tanh(\\mathbf c_t)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "![LSTM cell](/images/lstm-3.svg)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Why LSTM Works\n",
        "\n",
        "If:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf f_t \\approx 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Then:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial \\mathbf c_t}{\\partial \\mathbf c_{t-1}} \\approx 1\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        ">Gradient preserved.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tensorflow: LSTM"
      ],
      "id": "674a5577"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model = keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.LSTM(64, return_sequences=True),\n",
        "    layers.LSTM(32),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1)\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model.compile(optimizer=\"adam\", loss=\"mse\")"
      ],
      "id": "b7d3a360",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Gated Recurrent Unit (GRU)\n",
        "\n",
        "## GRU Equations\n",
        "\n",
        ">Simpler alternative to LSTM.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Update gate:**\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf z_t = \\sigma\\left(\\mathbf W_z [\\mathbf h_{t-1} \\, \\mathbf x_t] + \\mathbf b_z\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Reset gate:**\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf r_t = \\sigma\\left(\\mathbf W_r [\\mathbf h_{t-1} \\, \\mathbf x_t] + \\mathbf b_r\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Candidate cell state:**\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\widetilde{\\mathbf h}_t = \\tanh\\left(\\mathbf W_h [\\mathbf r_t \\! \\odot \\! \\mathbf h_{t-1} \\, \\mathbf x_t] + \\mathbf b_h\\right)\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "![GRU Cell Update](/images/gru-2.svg)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## GRU Update\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\mathbf h_t = (1 - \\mathbf z_t) \\odot \\mathbf h_{t-1} + \\mathbf z_t \\odot \\widetilde{\\mathbf h}_t\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "![GRU Cell](/images/gru-3.svg)\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tensorflow: GRU"
      ],
      "id": "164ccd02"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model = keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.GRU(64, return_sequences=True),\n",
        "    layers.GRU(32),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1)\n",
        "])"
      ],
      "id": "bd069db1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Regularization in RNNs\n",
        "\n",
        "## Recurrent Dropout\n",
        "\n",
        "Standard dropout disrupts temporal memory.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Recurrent dropout:**\n",
        "\n",
        "- Applied on recurrent connections\n",
        "- Same mask across timesteps\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## TensorFlow: Recurrent Dropout"
      ],
      "id": "b683fb67"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "model = keras.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.LSTM(\n",
        "        64,\n",
        "        return_sequences=True,\n",
        "        recurrent_dropout=0.2\n",
        "    ),\n",
        "    layers.LSTM(32),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1)\n",
        "])"
      ],
      "id": "6798fbba",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Gradient Clipping\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\nabla_{\\boldsymbol \\theta} \\mathscr L \\leftarrow \\frac{\\nabla_{\\boldsymbol \\theta} \\mathscr L}{\\max(1, \\frac{||\\nabla_{\\boldsymbol \\theta} \\mathscr L||}{\\lambda})}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Prevent exploding gradients:"
      ],
      "id": "dc373727"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "optimizer = tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(\n",
        "    learning_rate=0.001,\n",
        "    clipnorm=1.0\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "id": "d565bd28",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
